definition: the West/abbr. for Spain 西班牙[Xi1 ban1 ya2]/Spanish
ocean/sea/CL:個|个[ge4],片[pian4]/great number of people or things/(dialect) numerous

sentences.english: Almost thirty-four-million people live in the West Coast states.
sentences.chinese: 差不多有三千四百萬人居住在西海岸諸州。

sentences.english: In U. S. WestCoast, Also small earthquake constantly.
sentences.chinese: 在美國西海岸小地震，也不斷。

sentences.english: Detailed view of an iceberg calved from glaciers on west Greenlandic coast.
sentences.chinese: 格陵蘭西海岸冰川上脫落冰山的清晰圖像。

sentences.english: and then we have the nationals where we compete with the schools on the West Coast as well.
sentences.chinese: 然後我們有全國賽，我們也跟西海岸的學校比。

sentences.english: The Jersey Shore situation differs a bit.
sentences.chinese: 澤西海岸的情況有一點不同。

sentences.english: Yea, so is Snooky from Jersey Shore.
sentences.chinese: 對對，《澤西海岸》中的斯努基也是。

sentences.english: Hobbledehoy. An unusual mailbox seen on the road to Blackball, West Coast of New Zealand's South Island.
sentences.chinese: 醜男郵箱，一個位於新西蘭西海岸的不常見的郵箱。

sentences.english: Is there any competition between schools on the West Coast and schools on the East Coast?
sentences.chinese: 西海岸和東海岸的學校有競爭嗎？

sentences.english: Lishui is situated in Southwestern Zhejiang Province and adjacent to the west coast of the Pacific.
sentences.chinese: 麗水位於中國浙江省西南部，毗鄰太平洋西海岸。

sentences.english: Gioia says that action must now be taken to find and deal with the major West African sources of the pollutants.
sentences.chinese: 驕雅說必須採取行動查處非洲西海岸氯聯苯污染源。

sentences.english: She now lives in Stavanger at the west coast of Norway.
sentences.chinese: 現居挪威西海岸的斯塔萬格。

sentences.english: Or behold the flowing years from the Sea returning?
sentences.chinese: 誰能見，歲月流逝西海何時歸？

sentences.english: It is about 30km or 20 miles off the western coast of modern Turkey.
sentences.chinese: 它座落於現今的土耳其西海岸約30公里外。

sentences.english: A separate typhoon, Etau, slammed into Japan's west coast on Monday.
sentences.chinese: 另一場颱風“艾濤”週一襲擊日本西海岸。

sentences.english: Many made it to the west coast of Australia, where they were captured.
sentences.chinese: 很多人到達澳大利亞西海岸，並在那裏被俘。
